stem), the results are often not conclusive. Most of the time the overall environmental gain or loss is small, especially when an electric option is compared to a fossil alternative. The result will then also depend on the e\$ciency of the fossil option. If the demand-side option, on the other hand, creates possibilities for substantial changes in the supply-side structure, the results are dominated by the supply side. If the measure triggers the construction of a cleaner plant (e.g., a combined cycle gas-"red plant), or prevents the commissioning of a polluting plant (e.g., a coal-"red plant), it provides positive results. 2000 Elsevier Science Ltd. All rights reserved.},
